node.title: Remote NT community Beswick to enter a three-day lockout, Alice Springs wastewater tests positive to COVID-19
node.alt: Natasha Fyles at the Marrara testing clinic during lockdown in the NT.
node.description: NT Health Minister Natasha Fyles said authorities were concerned by COVID-positive wastewater detected in Beswick and Barunga.
node.content:
["The Northern Territory has recorded one\u00a0new local COVID-19 case linked to the Katherine cluster, Health Minister Natasha Fyles says.\u00a0", "Ms Fyles said the new case was a man in his 20s who tested positive to the virus during a COVID-19\u00a0testing blitz in Katherine East.\u00a0", "It brings the total cluster in the current outbreak to 68.", "She said authorities were \"concerned\" by COVID-positive wastewater detected in Beswick and Barunga.", "\u201cThis is a concerning development to health authorities, as we weren\u2019t expecting that,\u201d she said.", "The community of Beswick, which Ms Fyles said has a vaccination rate of 64 per cent, will go into a three-day lockout from 2pm today.", "\"We'll be\u00a0sending our rapid response team down to Beswick and they'll go into a 72-hour lockout and we'll be providing vaccinations to really lift that rate,\" Ms Fyles said.", "Barunga, which has a higher vaccination rate of about 91 per cent, will be subject to a mask mandate for the next three days.", "Acting Chief Health Officer Charles Pain said Beswick had\u00a0a \"very good first vaccination rate\", but its double-dose rate of 64 per cent is \"not adequate for us to feel comfortable\".", "\"Those measures that we put in place have been put in place to protect that community,\" he said.", "\"And we will do this, where necessary, to protect communities, particularly if their vaccination rates are not yet up to a level at which we feel comfortable.\"", "Ms Fyles said\u00a0authorities had detected COVID-positive wastewater at several locations in Katherine.", "\"We've got Martin Terrace, Stuart Highway and Bicentennial Road continuing to test positive,\" she said.", "She said about 800 COVID-19 tests were conducted in Katherine over the past few days.", "Positive wastewater has also been detected in Binjari, Rockhole and Warlpiri Camp.", "However Ms Fyles said this was to be expected given some residents had recently returned from quarantine at Howard Springs after recovering from the virus.", "
An undetected COVID-19 case could be in Alice Springs, say authorities
", "Wastewater in the Gillen and Northside catchments in Alice Springs has also tested positive to COVID, Ms Fyles said.", "Alice Springs is about 1,183 kilometres from Katherine, where most of the cases part of the latest outbreak have been based.", "Ms Fyles said at this stage authorities \"[couldn't] explain\" the results, although they could have come from people undertaking home quarantine in Alice Springs who have COVID-19 but had not yet tested positive.", "She said that, given the town's high vaccination rate, no COVID-19 prevention measures would be put in place, but \"we are watching Alice Springs very closely\".", "Dr Pain said it was possible a COVID-19 case was moving about the community in Alice Springs.", "\"We must be very cautious over these next 24-48 hours,\" he said.", "More wastewater testing results are due to come back today, he said.", "\"Please, in Alice Springs, do not be complacent,\" he said.", "\"We may have a positive case in the community. Please come forward and get tested if you have the slightest of symptoms and \u2026 come forward and get vaccinated.\"", "More to come.\u00a0"]
